# Icons, actions, and tables (Executiva Cloud)

**Accessible labels** (`aria-label`, `title`) should match the product language (**pt-BR**) where user-facing.

## Edit / Delete

- Import `typeMgmtEditIconBtn` and `typeMgmtDeleteIconBtn` from `components/ui/typeManagementStyles.ts`.
- Stroke color comes from `EditIcon`/`DeleteIcon` (`Icons.tsx`) via `currentColor`; do not duplicate SVGs with per-screen fixed colors.
- Pattern: `rounded-full`, `text-slate-500`, hover `bg-slate-100` + indigo/red. After standardization, avoid `text-slate-400` + `hover:bg-slate-200` for these pairs unless documented.

## “Actions” column

- `inline-flex flex-row flex-nowrap items-center justify-end`, cell `whitespace-nowrap text-right`, `<th>` `text-right` and `min-w-*` so icons stay on one line.
- Do not add informational columns without sustainable data.

## Domain-specific actions (e.g. Users)

- **Refresh list**: `RefreshIcon` (`Icons.tsx`); `title` + `aria-label`; avoid an infinite spinner as the primary control.
- **Invite / password**: `LockClosedIcon`; explanatory `title`/`aria-label`; loading with `aria-busy` / opacity — do not mimic a generic loader.
- **Deactivate**: `NoSymbolIcon` when the screen uses icon actions.

## Icon-only buttons

- Always `type="button"` outside submit flows, and **`aria-label`** (+ `title` for tooltip when useful).
